com.amadeus.android.domain.air.models

Class Defaults

  • com.amadeus.android.domain.air.models.Defaults

  • @JsonClass
public class Defaults

    the query parameters for which default values were used are returned here

    • Constructor Detail

      • Defaults

        public Defaults(@Json @Nullable
                java.lang.String departureDate,
                @Json @Nullable
                java.lang.Boolean oneWay,
                @Json @Nullable
                java.lang.String duration,
                @Json @Nullable
                java.lang.Boolean nonStop,
                @Json @Nullable
                com.amadeus.android.domain.air.models.Defaults.ViewByEnum viewBy)

        the query parameters for which default values were used are returned here

        Parameters:
        departureDate - the date, or range of dates, on which the flight will depart from the origin. Dates are specified in the ISO 8601 YYYY-MM-DD format, e.g. 2017-12-25. Ranges are specified with a comma and are inclusive
        oneWay - if this parameter is set to true, only one-way flights are considered. If this parameter is not set or set to false, only round-trip flights are considered
        duration - exact duration or range of durations of the travel, in days. This parameter must not be set if oneWay is true. Ranges are specified with a comma and are inclusive, e.g. 2,8
        nonStop - if this parameter is set to true, only flights going from the origin to the destination with no stop in-between are considered
        viewBy - view the flight destinations by COUNTRY, DATE, DESTINATION, DURATION, or WEEK. View by COUNTRY to get the cheapest flight dates for every country in the given range. View by DATE to get the cheapest flight dates for every departure date in the given range. View by DURATION to get the cheapest flight dates for every departure date and for every duration in the given ranges. View by WEEK to get the cheapest flight destination for every week in the given range of departure dates
